('Judges', 11, 'kids', 1, 'What was Jephthah known as because of his mother?', 'Son of a harlot', 'Son of a king', 'Son of a priest', 'Son of a prophet', 'a', 'Judges 11:1 — "Now Jephthah the Gileadite was a mighty man of valour, and he was the son of an harlot."'),
('Judges', 11, 'kids', 2, 'Which nation did Jephthah fight against to save Israel?', 'The children of Ammon', 'The Philistines', 'The Moabites', 'The Amalekites', 'a', 'Judges 11:32 — "So Jephthah passed over unto the children of Ammon to fight against them; and the LORD delivered them into his hands."'),
('Judges', 11, 'kids', 3, 'What rash vow did Jephthah make before going into battle?', 'He would offer whatever came out of his house first as a burnt offering', 'He would fast for forty days', 'He would build an altar to God', 'He would give half his wealth to the priests', 'a', 'Judges 11:31 — "then it shall be, that whatsoever cometh forth of the doors of my house to meet me...I will offer it up for a burnt offering."');
