('Judges', 15, 'kids', 2, 'What unusual weapon did Samson use to kill one thousand Philistines?', 'The jawbone of an ass', 'A wooden club', 'A stone from the field', 'An iron sword', 'a', 'Judges 15:15 — "And he found a new jawbone of an ass, and put forth his hand, and took it, and slew a thousand men therewith."'),
('Judges', 15, 'kids', 3, 'After the great battle, Samson was thirsty. Where did his water miraculously come from?', 'From a hollow place in the jawbone', 'From a spring that burst out of the ground nearby', 'From a well that appeared in the desert', 'From rain that fell from heaven', 'a', 'Judges 15:19 — "But God clave an hollow place that was in the jaw, and there came water thereout; and when he had drunk, his spirit came again."');
