('Judges', 16, 'kids', 1, 'What was the name of the woman whom Delilah worked for and who paid her to discover Samson''s secret?', 'The lords of the Philistines', 'The king of Gaza', 'The priests of Dagon', 'The soldiers of Samson''s enemies', 'a', 'Judges 16:5 — "And the lords of the Philistines came up unto her, and said unto her, Entice him, and see wherein his great strength lieth."'),
('Judges', 16, 'kids', 2, 'What was the true secret of Samson''s strength?', 'His hair had never been cut because he was a Nazirite', 'He wore a special golden belt given by God', 'He ate from a magical tree in Israel', 'He prayed three times every day without fail', 'a', 'Judges 16:17 — "There hath not come a razor upon mine head; for I have been a Nazarite unto God from my mother''s womb: and if I be shaven, then my strength will go from me."'),
('Judges', 16, 'kids', 3, 'What did Samson do at the end of his life that killed him and all the Philistines around him?', 'He pushed the two middle pillars of the temple, causing it to fall on everyone inside', 'He called fire from heaven on the Philistine army', 'He picked up the temple gates and threw them', 'He released three hundred foxes with torches inside the temple', 'a', 'Judges 16:30 — "And Samson said, Let me die with the Philistines. And he bowed himself with all his might; and the house fell upon the lords, and upon all the people that were therein."');
