-- ═══ Judges Chapter 17 ═══
-- Kids
('Judges', 17, 'kids', 1, 'What did Micah''s mother use the silver for after he returned it to her?', 'To make a graven image and a molten image', 'To buy land in Ephraim', 'To give to the tabernacle at Shiloh', 'To pay for a wedding feast', 'a', 'Judges 17:4 — "Yet he restored the money unto his mother; and his mother took two hundred shekels of silver, and gave them to the founder, who made thereof a graven image and a molten image."'),
('Judges', 17, 'kids', 2, 'Micah set up a household shrine with an idol. What kind of religious leader did he set up to serve at it?', 'One of his own sons, and later a Levite', 'A priest from the tabernacle at Shiloh', 'An elder from the tribe of Judah', 'A foreign seer from Canaan', 'a', 'Judges 17:5 — "And the man Micah had an house of gods, and made an ephod, and teraphim, and consecrated one of his sons, who became his priest." Later in verse 12 he ordained a Levite.'),
('Judges', 17, 'kids', 3, 'What verse in this chapter tells us the spiritual condition of Israel at this time?', '"In those days there was no king in Israel, but every man did that which was right in his own eyes"', '"The children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the LORD"', '"There was no priest in Israel and no law was kept"', '"Every tribe went its own way and forgot the covenant"', 'a', 'Judges 17:6 — "In those days there was no king in Israel, but every man did that which was right in his own eyes." This is the theological refrain that appears twice more in the closing chapters.');
