('Judges', 19, 'kids', 2, 'Who offered the Levite and his party hospitality in Gibeah?', 'An old man from the hill country of Ephraim', 'The ruler of the city', 'A Levite from the tribe of Levi', 'A widow who lived near the gate', 'a', 'Judges 19:16-20 — "And, behold, there came an old man from his work out of the field at even...and the old man said, Peace be with thee; howsoever let all thy wants lie upon me."'),
('Judges', 19, 'kids', 3, 'What terrible thing did the wicked men of Gibeah do?', 'They abused and killed the Levite''s concubine throughout the night', 'They robbed the Levite and drove him out of the city', 'They burned the old man''s house down', 'They attacked the Levite with swords', 'a', 'Judges 19:25 — "But the men would not hearken to him: so the man took his concubine, and brought her forth unto them; and they knew her, and abused her all the night until the morning."');
